# TradeIQ - AI Development Rules
# This file is automatically read by Cursor IDE
# Version: 1.0.0 | 2026-05-17

## CRITICAL: Before ANY code change, you MUST:

1. READ the file you're about to modify (use Read tool, never guess content)
2. PLAN your changes and present them before executing
3. USE Edit/MultiEdit for existing files (NEVER use Write to overwrite)
4. VERIFY with `bun run lint` after changes
5. UPDATE CHANGELOG.md for every functional change

## Project: TradeIQ
- Stack: Next.js 16, TypeScript, Prisma + SQLite, shadcn/ui, Tailwind, lightweight-charts v5
- Repo: https://github.com/yecos/TradeIQ
- Language: Spanish for UI/docs, English for code/variables

## 10 Golden Rules

### R1 - READ FIRST
Never write code without reading the target file first.

### R2 - EDIT, DON'T OVERWRITE
Use Edit/MultiEdit for surgical changes. Only use Write for NEW files.

### R3 - DOCUMENT EVERY CHANGE
Update CHANGELOG.md after every functional change.
Format: FEATURE/FIX/CHANGE/REFACTOR/CHORE + file + description

### R4 - VERIFY AFTER CHANGES
Run `bun run lint` after each significant change. Fix errors before continuing.

### R5 - DON'T BREAK INTERFACES
Never change an exported function/type signature without updating ALL dependent files.
Critical files: types.ts, confluence-engine.ts, market-data.ts, schema.prisma

### R6 - PLAN BEFORE CODE
Present a plan with: files to modify, specific changes, affected dependencies,
breaking risk, verification method. WAIT for approval before executing.

### R7 - UPDATE WORKLOG
At session end, update worklog.md with: Task ID, steps taken, results, files changed.

### R8 - NO SECRETS IN CODE
Never hardcode API keys, tokens, or secrets. Use environment variables.

### R9 - SEPARATION OF CONCERNS
- Business logic → src/lib/ (not in components)
- UI → src/components/ (not in lib)
- Data access → provider pattern (not direct fetch in components)
- API routes → thin controllers that call lib/

### R10 - STRICT TYPESCRIPT
No `any` without explicit justification. Define types for everything.

## Architecture Map
```
src/lib/types.ts              ← CRITICAL (everyone depends on this)
src/lib/confluence-engine.ts  ← CRITICAL (core business logic)
src/lib/technical-analysis.ts ← RSI, MACD, Bollinger, EMA, ADX, ATR
src/lib/pattern-detection.ts  ← Candlestick patterns
src/lib/volume-analysis.ts    ← OBV, Accumulation/Distribution
src/lib/market-data.ts        ← Mock data provider
src/lib/vector-definitions.ts ← 6 configurable vectors
src/lib/store.ts              ← Zustand store
src/app/api/                  ← 7 API endpoints
src/components/trading/       ← 7 trading components
prisma/schema.prisma          ← 6 DB models
```

## Session Flow
1. Read WORKFLOW.md + CHANGELOG.md + relevant files
2. Present plan → WAIT for approval
3. Execute changes surgically
4. Verify with lint
5. Update CHANGELOG.md
6. Update worklog.md at session end

## For full details, read WORKFLOW.md in the repo root.
